# flex-testing-agent

Local Python harness for a physical Opentrons Flex (**KansasFLEX**). The harness is the product; Cursor/Claude/MCP are adapters.

## Layering (extend in this order)

1. **Atomic clients** (`src/flex_testing_agent/clients/`) – thin async httpx wrappers for robot HTTP APIs
2. **Capabilities** (`src/flex_testing_agent/capabilities/`) – compose clients with risk, gates, evidence
3. **Scenarios / orchestration** – locks, run context, mutation gates, persistence
4. **CLI** (`flex-test`) or future adapters – thin entrypoints only

Do not invent parallel HTTP stacks, arbitrary shell, or ad-hoc robot URLs from agents.

## Existing surface to reuse

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Session + headers | `clients/session.py` |
| Health / update / auth detect | `clients/health.py`, `update_health.py`, `auth_settings.py` |
| Read-only catalog + probe | `clients/readonly.py`, `capabilities/probe.py` |
| Camera | `clients/camera.py` |
| Install / update | `clients/update.py`, `capabilities/install.py` |
| Releases | `releases/` |
| Flex facade | `robots/flex.py` |
| Gates | `orchestration/gates.py` |
| Docs | `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/safety-model.md` |

## Extension rules

- Prefer new **client methods** over one-off httpx in capabilities/CLI
- New robot operations need a `CapabilityDescriptor` + risk level + gate checks
- Catalog new GET paths in `READONLY_ENDPOINTS` when adding read-only API coverage
- Call `opentrons/opentrons` the **monorepo**; research clone at `upstream/opentrons`
- Point-release docs: `docs/monorepo-releases.md` (`chore_release-X.Y.Z` cherry-picks / mergebacks)
- Publish robot test plans as YAML in `docs/test-suggestions/`; `make pages` / Pages workflow on `main`
- Package/CLI name: `flex_testing_agent` / `flex-test`; Python 3.12+; use `uv`

## Commands

```bash
uv sync --all-extras
make lint          # ruff + mypy (required after code changes)
make test
uv run flex-test inspect|probe|releases|put <version>
```
